 benefits from greater affluence. Action is needed - but to increase abundance and spread it worldwide, not to limit prosperity, as the sceptics would have it. The lively and provocative hardback edition was published to widespread coverage in 2010, and triggered debate and dissent in equal measure.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aEconomic developmentxSocial aspects. 0aEconomic development. 0aWealth. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Policy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z9783111196213oZDB-23-BUPP0 cprintz978184742345040uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781847423474?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847423474423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847423474/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-BUPPc1995d2013